Nerac Launches eVigilant, New Web Tracking Product; Clients Now Receive Updated Web Information Automatically

Author: Business Editors/High-Tech Writers

Publication info: Business Wire ; New York [New York]03 Feb 2003: 1.

https://search.proquest.com/wire-feeds/nerac-launches-evigilant-new-web-tracking-product/docview/446382904/se-2?accountid=37662

Abstract: "Through a test market approached in December and January, Nerac subscribers had remarkable success with eVigilant and most have reported saving time in searching for information on the Internet," said Gerri Potash, Vice President of Client Services at Nerac. "Because eVigilant takes information directly from the original source of a Web page, several eVigilant users have stated that they are now receiving information faster, before learning of it second- hand."

Full text: TOLLAND, Conn.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Feb. 3, 2003--Leading information service Nerac announced a launch today of eVigilant, a new product that delivers updated Web page information right to a client's e-mail. Providing e-mail alerts on revised Web pages, eVigilant consolidates Web site tracking into a single e-mail of topics, saving a significant amount of time and energy.
"As reliable resources become more prevalent on the Internet, companies and organizations are using their Web sites as information tools," said Kevin Bouley, President of Nerac. "Keeping up with frequently revolving content is time consuming. eVigilant brings new Web information to the user, saving them hours of searching every week."
Virtually any text published on a Web page can be tracked using eVigilant. Nerac clients can use eVigilant to track companies, products, events, news and moneymaking opportunities.
To set up an eVigilant profile, Nerac's Information Specialists work directly with clients to help select pages for Web tracking. When the selected Web pages are updated, subscribers receive an e- mail within 24 hours that lists the content revisions and a link to view the page. Through the eVigilant link, subscribers view a page that highlights text changes, providing a quick review of the new information.
"Through a test market approached in December and January, Nerac subscribers had remarkable success with eVigilant and most have reported saving time in searching for information on the Internet," said Gerri Potash, Vice President of Client Services at Nerac. "Because eVigilant takes information directly from the original source of a Web page, several eVigilant users have stated that they are now receiving information faster, before learning of it second- hand."
To learn more about eVigilant and how your company can become a Nerac subscriber, contact a Nerac representative at 860-872-7000, Monday-Friday, 7:00 a.m.-7:00 p.m., Eastern Time.
About Nerac
Nerac has been delivering cutting-edge technical information to scientists and engineers since 1966. With access to nearly every journal article and conference paper published in the last 37 years, Nerac's in-house database collection effectively serves clients in a variety of industries. Nerac's nearly 100 Information Specialists access a dedicated computing environment to provide information from resources that include international engineering, scientific, patent and business databases as well as professional contacts. Based in Tolland, CT, Nerac provides information services globally via the Web.

